  "why": "DistXplore aims to produce realistic/valid inputs and enforces naturalness through constrained, conservative image transformations (e.g., translation, rotation, brightness), use of Lp-based validity constraints, and an explicit validity check (manual evaluation showing high validity ratios). However, the method performs iterative population-level genetic search (crossover + per-iteration mutations) without an explicit mechanism described that constrains cumulative distortion relative to the original seed across many iterations. In other words, the paper enforces naturalness/validity at each mutation step (and reports high human-checked validity), but does not describe controls that prevent drift accumulating across iterations relative to the original seed. Semantic-consistency (same-label equivalence) is not required by the oracle used in the paper (they generate valid OOD data and do not assume mutated inputs keep the original seed label), so that dimension is not applicable. Given that only per-step naturalness is enforced (not explicit bounds preventing cumulative drift w.r.t. original seeds), the appropriate rating is Medium.",
